        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "briefDescription": "The scheme \"Working Women Hostel\" by the Women and Child Development Department, Government of Haryana aims to provide safe and affordable accommodation to working women. Through this scheme, hostel facilities at subsidized rent are provided to employed women.\n\n",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &amp;quot;Working Women Hostel&amp;quot; by the Women and Child Development Department, Government of Haryana aims to provide secure, affordable, and conveniently located housing to employed women to enable them to become socially and economically independent. The scheme also intends to ensure a supportive environment for working women, particularly those away from their homes. The scheme is implemented by the respective designated implementing organizations managing the hostels. These hostels are meant to serve women who are working professionals and need residential support in cities or towns where they are employed.\n",
        "benefits_md": "&gt; **Rental Charges:**\n\n\n  - **Single Bedrooms:** Not exceeding 15% of total emoluments/gross salary.  - **Double Bedrooms:** Not exceeding 10% of total emoluments/gross salary.  - **Dormitories:** Not exceeding 7.5% of total emoluments/gross salary.\n",
        "exclusions_md": "",
